1
00:01:26,300 --> 00:01:28,230
One moment, I'll
turn on the lights.

2
00:01:29,570 --> 00:01:31,010
Could you follow me?

3
00:01:34,970 --> 00:01:37,190
<i>KIM Da-mi</i>

4
00:01:37,210 --> 00:01:39,640
The gallery is downstairs.

5
00:01:40,110 --> 00:01:41,790
Watch your step.

6
00:01:41,810 --> 00:01:42,810
<i>JEON So-nee</i>

7
00:01:44,640 --> 00:01:46,290
This way, please.

8
00:01:46,330 --> 00:01:47,520
<i>BYUN Woo-seok</i>

9
00:01:49,870 --> 00:01:53,550
<i>Directed by MIN Yong-keun</i>

10
00:02:05,540 --> 00:02:06,730
This is you, right?

11
00:02:09,940 --> 00:02:10,930
Take a closer look.

12
00:02:11,740 --> 00:02:14,410
It look like a photo
but it's a drawing.

13
00:02:19,840 --> 00:02:21,290
It's hyperrealism.

14
00:02:21,830 --> 00:02:24,360
This entire drawing
was done with a pencil.

15
00:02:26,990 --> 00:02:30,660
This piece won our
gallery's recent contest,

16
00:02:30,750 --> 00:02:33,790
aside from the name 'Ha-eun, '
there was no other information.

17
00:02:39,130 --> 00:02:43,520
The director would like to
sign her as in-house artist,

18
00:02:43,580 --> 00:02:44,760
but we can't reach her.

19
00:02:44,820 --> 00:02:46,940
We sent an email
but no response.

20
00:02:48,630 --> 00:02:51,030
I know that she's
close friends with you.

21
00:02:52,090 --> 00:02:55,750
If you're in touch with her,
could you introduce us?

22
00:02:55,820 --> 00:02:57,470
I don't really know her.

23
00:02:58,130 --> 00:03:00,400
We had run-ins as children.

24
00:03:01,980 --> 00:03:04,190
That wasn't the case at all.

25
00:03:06,280 --> 00:03:09,120
While searching
online with her email,

26
00:03:09,160 --> 00:03:11,700
we came across a blog.

27
00:03:11,970 --> 00:03:13,300
<i>Summer Milky Way</i>

28
00:03:13,370 --> 00:03:15,460
There were posts about you two.

29
00:03:17,700 --> 00:03:20,210
It looked like you
two were very close.

30
00:03:21,300 --> 00:03:24,500
This is a printout of the blog.

31
00:03:27,980 --> 00:03:31,450
<i>Ahn Mi-so / Ko Ha-eun</i>

32
00:03:33,280 --> 00:03:36,770
I'm sorry, I can't help you.

33
00:03:43,950 --> 00:03:44,950
Mi-so!

34
00:03:55,940 --> 00:03:56,750
It's been a while.

35
00:03:57,480 --> 00:04:01,000
Yeah, indeed.

36
00:04:03,090 --> 00:04:06,460
Are you in touch with Ha-eun?

37
00:04:08,260 --> 00:04:09,610
We lost touch a while ago.

38
00:04:10,720 --> 00:04:12,520
I thought you two would last.

39
00:04:13,010 --> 00:04:14,830
We were kids back then.

40
00:04:15,570 --> 00:04:17,620
By the way, what
brings you here?

41
00:04:17,940 --> 00:04:19,220
Mr. Ham Jin-woo?

42
00:04:19,760 --> 00:04:21,740
- Hello.
- Evening.

43
00:04:22,350 --> 00:04:23,360
One sec.

44
00:04:25,350 --> 00:04:27,650
Thank you for coming.

45
00:04:27,750 --> 00:04:29,270
I'm curator Kang Mal-geum.

46
00:04:29,340 --> 00:04:30,340
Hi.

47
00:04:30,410 --> 00:04:32,320
Shall we talk inside?

48
00:04:33,540 --> 00:04:34,380
Mi-so!

49
00:04:43,700 --> 00:04:46,240
<i>Spring, 2001, Graduation</i>

50
00:04:56,460 --> 00:04:59,050
<i>Summer Milky Way</i>

51
00:05:03,670 --> 00:05:04,530
<i>Summer, 1998</i>

52
00:05:04,570 --> 00:05:08,070
<i>I remember the cicadas
when I think about those days.</i>

53
00:05:09,210 --> 00:05:12,160
<i>They sounded sluggish somehow.</i>

54
00:05:13,880 --> 00:05:17,280
<i>It was a hot day, and
the class was boring.</i>

55
00:05:18,090 --> 00:05:21,860
<i>One that sluggish
day, you came along.</i>

56
00:05:22,030 --> 00:05:26,900
'Who' is gathering
'what' from 'where'?

57
00:05:27,030 --> 00:05:30,780
Now, we can replace 'who'
with 'aunt', and 'what' with...

58
00:05:31,150 --> 00:05:33,020
- Location.
- That's right.

59
00:05:33,490 --> 00:05:34,490
One moment.

60
00:05:36,970 --> 00:05:37,970
Hello.

61
00:05:38,170 --> 00:05:40,320
I brought you the new student.

62
00:05:40,390 --> 00:05:41,390
I see.

63
00:05:42,600 --> 00:05:43,710
Come in.

64
00:05:45,930 --> 00:05:49,000
We got a new student from Seoul.

65
00:05:49,800 --> 00:05:51,640
Could you introduce yourself?

66
00:05:53,290 --> 00:05:54,640
Ahn Mi-so.

67
00:05:55,040 --> 00:05:57,400
Ahn Mi-so.

68
00:05:57,460 --> 00:06:02,740
And? Do you want to say
anything to the class?

69
00:06:05,290 --> 00:06:08,850
All right, do you see that desk?

70
00:06:09,450 --> 00:06:10,800
Go sit over there.

71
00:06:18,510 --> 00:06:21,420
Okay, let's continue.

72
00:06:21,540 --> 00:06:25,050
'Where' is where? What is this referring to?

73
00:06:26,320 --> 00:06:29,740
So this has to be a location.

74
00:06:29,850 --> 00:06:33,060
And when referring
to gathering...

75
00:06:33,140 --> 00:06:34,140
Ahn Mi-so!

76
00:06:36,110 --> 00:06:37,410
Ahn Mi-so!

77
00:06:39,260 --> 00:06:40,620
Get back here!

78
00:06:41,980 --> 00:06:45,560
Ahn Mi-so!
Stop right there!

79
00:06:52,440 --> 00:06:53,440
Hey!

80
00:06:55,120 --> 00:06:56,220
Ahn Mi-so!

81
00:07:02,420 --> 00:07:03,620
Your bag!

82
00:07:04,590 --> 00:07:07,400
Take it, you left it.

83
00:07:08,280 --> 00:07:11,930
come up, stairs are over there!

84
00:07:14,590 --> 00:07:15,590
Why not?

85
00:07:16,630 --> 00:07:19,480
I can't go anywhere
high, I'm scared.

86
00:07:22,040 --> 00:07:25,490
When you're scared, just squint.

87
00:07:27,090 --> 00:07:28,770
It's less scary.

88
00:07:40,020 --> 00:07:41,260
What's your name?

89
00:07:43,040 --> 00:07:44,040
Ko Ha-eun.

90
00:07:45,200 --> 00:07:46,200
Ha-eun?

91
00:07:48,020 --> 00:07:51,640
Does it mean 'summer'
and 'Milky Way'?

92
00:07:53,370 --> 00:07:54,740
Summer Milky Way?

93
00:07:54,870 --> 00:07:57,470
Not for Milky Way,
it means 'gentle'.

94
00:07:57,810 --> 00:08:00,310
'Gentle summer' is boring.

95
00:08:00,390 --> 00:08:02,050
Go with 'Summer Milky Way.'

96
00:08:03,260 --> 00:08:05,880
The 'Mi-so' literally
means smile?

97
00:08:07,170 --> 00:08:08,320
Probably.

98
00:08:09,990 --> 00:08:11,460
Then why don't you ever smile?

99
00:08:12,090 --> 00:08:13,510
I don't?

100
00:08:13,930 --> 00:08:19,100
No, not at school,
not right now.

101
00:08:23,190 --> 00:08:28,590
Because Ahn means 'not'?

102
00:09:01,070 --> 00:09:03,410
She's drenched.

103
00:09:03,930 --> 00:09:05,320
It's okay.

104
00:09:07,560 --> 00:09:09,240
What do we do?

105
00:09:10,430 --> 00:09:12,200
It's okay, kitty.

106
00:09:12,530 --> 00:09:14,460
Could you wipe her?

107
00:09:14,520 --> 00:09:15,530
What's that?

108
00:09:17,270 --> 00:09:22,100
She was alone in the
rain, so I brought her.

109
00:09:22,750 --> 00:09:23,750
And her?

110
00:09:26,950 --> 00:09:27,950
My friend.

111
00:09:34,060 --> 00:09:35,800
Wash up quickly, let's eat.

112
00:10:02,410 --> 00:10:05,170
Isn't it stuffy wearing these?

113
00:10:05,730 --> 00:10:06,730
It is.

114
00:10:08,100 --> 00:10:10,250
- Why do you wear it?
- I dunno.

115
00:10:11,030 --> 00:10:14,140
Girls are supposed
to suck it up,

116
00:10:14,270 --> 00:10:16,090
so it becomes comfy later.

117
00:10:18,000 --> 00:10:22,290
I won't wear it when I
grow up, I hate feeling stuffy.

118
00:10:32,180 --> 00:10:35,450
Ha-eun, not again?

119
00:10:36,510 --> 00:10:38,520
Carrots are sucky.

120
00:10:38,650 --> 00:10:40,560
I told you eat
what you're given.

121
00:10:40,640 --> 00:10:43,130
Your mom and I raised
the crop ourselves.

122
00:10:43,230 --> 00:10:44,620
I still hate it!

123
00:10:44,810 --> 00:10:46,820
Put them back in.

124
00:10:46,870 --> 00:10:48,890
You're embarrassing
yourself in front of your friend!

125
00:10:48,930 --> 00:10:51,410
Let her be, don't
force it on her!

126
00:10:51,460 --> 00:10:53,340
She'll eat it herself
when she grows up.

127
00:10:53,430 --> 00:10:56,560
She became a picky eater
because you baby her.

128
00:10:56,600 --> 00:10:58,200
Eat what you're given.

129
00:10:58,280 --> 00:11:01,670
That's enough, you're stubborn
like others in your family.

130
00:11:01,750 --> 00:11:03,280
Not at the table...

131
00:11:11,780 --> 00:11:13,580
I can't eat these...

132
00:11:17,620 --> 00:11:18,730
But I like carrots.

133
00:11:19,270 --> 00:11:21,350
Cool! I'll eat broccoli.

134
00:11:21,980 --> 00:11:23,630
Problem solved.

135
00:11:23,760 --> 00:11:26,960
Carrots for Mi-so,
broccoli for Ha-eun.

136
00:11:27,070 --> 00:11:28,190
Happy?

137
00:11:28,360 --> 00:11:29,360
Jeez!

138
00:11:29,440 --> 00:11:30,440
Here.

139
00:11:31,120 --> 00:11:32,120
One sec.

140
00:11:32,960 --> 00:11:33,960
Here.

141
00:11:41,290 --> 00:11:43,460
Good evening, I'm so sorry.

142
00:11:43,520 --> 00:11:44,270
Hello...

143
00:11:46,040 --> 00:11:47,040
Come here.

144
00:11:53,600 --> 00:11:56,620
Can't you call me and
tell me where you are?

145
00:11:56,720 --> 00:12:00,170
And why did you run off like
that, you embarrassed me.

146
00:12:00,280 --> 00:12:01,860
I said I don't want
to go to school.

147
00:12:02,490 --> 00:12:04,040
I'll transfer again soon anyway.

148
00:12:04,100 --> 00:12:05,690
I told you, not this time!

149
00:12:05,730 --> 00:12:07,550
You said the same
thing in Bucheon.

150
00:12:08,040 --> 00:12:09,890
And Gangneung too.

151
00:12:11,030 --> 00:12:12,220
How many times
already this year?

152
00:12:12,280 --> 00:12:13,280
Ahn Mi-so!

153
00:12:14,030 --> 00:12:16,840
When his situation improves,
he'll bring us back to Seoul!

154
00:12:16,940 --> 00:12:19,460
You're not the only
one, I'm sick of this too!

155
00:12:21,680 --> 00:12:24,020
You only care about yourself...

156
00:12:59,030 --> 00:13:03,500
It looks the same,
will you be an artist?

157
00:13:04,980 --> 00:13:05,990
No.

158
00:13:06,180 --> 00:13:08,350
Why? You draw so well.

159
00:13:09,850 --> 00:13:12,910
Dad said artist starve to death.

160
00:13:14,640 --> 00:13:15,880
Try it too.

161
00:13:16,790 --> 00:13:18,350
I don't draw so well...

162
00:13:18,930 --> 00:13:22,200
Doesn't matter, anyone can draw.

163
00:13:32,530 --> 00:13:36,380
What should we call her?

164
00:13:39,030 --> 00:13:41,170
I have a name in mind.

165
00:13:42,070 --> 00:13:43,070
What?

166
00:13:45,060 --> 00:13:46,060
'Mom'.

167
00:13:46,810 --> 00:13:47,810
'Mom'?

168
00:13:48,750 --> 00:13:51,030
You can't call a cat that.

169
00:13:51,110 --> 00:13:53,250
But you can call
it affectionately.

170
00:13:54,210 --> 00:13:55,210
Mom!

171
00:13:56,470 --> 00:13:58,070
Mom!

172
00:14:00,190 --> 00:14:01,600
Mom!

173
00:14:11,190 --> 00:14:14,530
This is her?
Which way is up?

174
00:14:18,100 --> 00:14:21,850
These are eyes, legs here.

175
00:14:24,980 --> 00:14:26,420
And her feelings.

176
00:14:27,622 --> 00:14:28,706
Feelings?

177
00:14:29,830 --> 00:14:31,400
You drew that too?

178
00:14:32,630 --> 00:14:33,630
Yeah!

179
00:14:35,280 --> 00:14:36,400
Is it weird?

180
00:14:38,440 --> 00:14:39,440
No.

181
00:14:47,110 --> 00:14:52,930
<i>That's when I first realized,
feelings can be drawn too.</i>

182
00:14:54,410 --> 00:14:57,360
<i>You'd moved me with
weird words at times.</i>

183
00:15:01,380 --> 00:15:04,580
<i>Same thing happened
when your mom moved back.</i>

184
00:15:07,000 --> 00:15:09,870
<i>I didn't say anything
and just felt sad,</i>

185
00:15:12,140 --> 00:15:16,500
<i>but you said we'd
never be apart.</i>

186
00:15:18,430 --> 00:15:20,490
<i>You'd rather stay in Jeju alone.</i>

187
00:15:23,120 --> 00:15:25,670
<i>We were able to stay together</i>

188
00:15:27,220 --> 00:15:29,570
<i>because of what you said.</i>

189
00:15:46,660 --> 00:15:48,170
Mi-so.

190
00:15:48,290 --> 00:15:49,680
You think you're Picasso?

191
00:15:50,420 --> 00:15:52,730
Stick with the basics, okay?

192
00:15:52,820 --> 00:15:54,000
Okay.

193
00:16:08,190 --> 00:16:10,440
<i>Skip class and come
out to the front gate.</i>

194
00:16:10,510 --> 00:16:15,540
Then this poetry is
about waiting for peonies,

195
00:16:15,590 --> 00:16:18,780
and sadness that came
after spring, but he still waits.

196
00:16:18,860 --> 00:16:24,850
It's a misconception that
peonies symbolize 'independence'.

197
00:16:28,515 --> 00:16:30,480
What's wrong?
You got a fever?

198
00:16:30,530 --> 00:16:35,150
I had a sore throat
since the morning...

199
00:16:35,670 --> 00:16:38,210
I think the fever's
getting worse.

200
00:16:38,360 --> 00:16:40,070
All right, head home
and get some rest.

201
00:16:45,970 --> 00:16:47,710
Ko Ha-eun!

202
00:16:49,100 --> 00:16:53,650
Ha-eun, you're evolving.

203
00:16:55,020 --> 00:16:57,450
It felt so stuffy,
I almost died.

204
00:16:58,720 --> 00:17:01,520
I had club activity, so I
left, no one looks for me.

205
00:17:01,660 --> 00:17:03,020
What's going on today?

206
00:17:03,120 --> 00:17:05,870
Your birthday's tomorrow,
let's get your ears pierced.

207
00:17:06,490 --> 00:17:08,260
Why do that for my birthday?

208
00:17:08,330 --> 00:17:11,480
Or you'll never get pierced.

209
00:17:12,040 --> 00:17:13,040
What?

210
00:17:13,380 --> 00:17:17,870
You need someone to
push you into doing it.

211
00:17:18,040 --> 00:17:20,870
It's good for blood
circulation too,

212
00:17:21,020 --> 00:17:24,160
it's good for you, me,
someone's sister, and others too.

213
00:17:24,210 --> 00:17:25,890
Bullshitting again.

214
00:17:28,690 --> 00:17:30,130
One, two, three, four!

215
00:18:25,600 --> 00:18:28,230
One, two, three!

216
00:18:30,360 --> 00:18:32,380
You did good.

217
00:18:34,630 --> 00:18:38,240
It really doesn't hurt?

218
00:18:38,680 --> 00:18:41,290
It stings for a second.

219
00:18:41,380 --> 00:18:44,320
Pain is temporary, and
pleasure is permanent.

220
00:18:45,250 --> 00:18:46,790
It's not the other way?

221
00:18:46,880 --> 00:18:48,940
No, it changed recently.

222
00:18:51,500 --> 00:18:53,030
One, two...

223
00:18:53,050 --> 00:18:54,490
Hold on!

224
00:18:55,120 --> 00:18:57,610
You have to do it
after three, okay?

225
00:18:57,660 --> 00:18:59,580
Don't do it on three.

226
00:18:59,630 --> 00:19:04,070
I'll count to three, and then do
it, so stay still, or you'll get hurt.

227
00:19:05,590 --> 00:19:07,550
One, two, three!

228
00:19:10,880 --> 00:19:12,220
What was that?

229
00:19:13,430 --> 00:19:16,330
Why did that fall?

230
00:19:16,390 --> 00:19:19,480
Oh man, come on...

231
00:19:19,540 --> 00:19:22,270
Did you knock them
over with your bag?

232
00:19:22,320 --> 00:19:24,550
No, I wasn't doing anything,

233
00:19:24,590 --> 00:19:27,410
they just fell by themselves.

234
00:19:27,480 --> 00:19:29,210
How could they
fall on their own?

235
00:19:29,270 --> 00:19:30,750
What a load of crap.

236
00:19:30,960 --> 00:19:34,530
Those cost over
$100, what did you do?

237
00:19:34,640 --> 00:19:37,540
How could they cost that much?

238
00:19:37,580 --> 00:19:39,230
They look a few bucks each.

239
00:19:39,310 --> 00:19:40,620
We'll compensate you.

240
00:19:40,710 --> 00:19:43,940
If thet're so expensive,
why put them by the door?

241
00:19:44,030 --> 00:19:45,030
Stop it.

242
00:19:45,120 --> 00:19:46,340
Sir, we'll pay you for them.

243
00:19:46,380 --> 00:19:48,560
I've never seen such a brat!

244
00:19:48,640 --> 00:19:51,030
You broke them, yet
you show no remorse.

245
00:19:51,410 --> 00:19:52,620
Which school do you go to?

246
00:19:52,680 --> 00:19:55,380
You look like a
trade school student.

247
00:19:56,950 --> 00:19:58,600
Are you badmouthing
trade schools?

248
00:19:59,660 --> 00:20:03,630
You got an anger issue,
you dumb trade schooler!

249
00:20:04,250 --> 00:20:06,610
Sir, don't do that!

250
00:20:06,720 --> 00:20:08,100
We got a set of lunatics!

251
00:20:08,200 --> 00:20:10,060
Ha-eun, let's just go,
he's not worth the fight.

252
00:20:10,350 --> 00:20:11,760
Where are you going?
Get back here!

253
00:20:11,980 --> 00:20:13,980
Pay for the damages!

254
00:20:14,030 --> 00:20:15,530
Get back here!

255
00:20:19,540 --> 00:20:20,540
You brats!

256
00:20:29,800 --> 00:20:31,160
You bitches!

257
00:20:34,430 --> 00:20:35,900
Just wait till I catch you!

258
00:20:36,680 --> 00:20:38,180
Stop right there!

259
00:20:40,610 --> 00:20:41,910
Stop, you brats!

260
00:20:44,010 --> 00:20:46,540
I'm gonna kill you two!

261
00:20:48,880 --> 00:20:49,940
I'll see you in a bit!

262
00:20:50,650 --> 00:20:51,650
What?

263
00:20:54,540 --> 00:20:56,490
You said you'll pay!

264
00:20:56,560 --> 00:20:59,840
Stop right there!
Just pay the cost price!

265
00:21:21,060 --> 00:21:22,060
Mi-so.

266
00:21:22,160 --> 00:21:23,640
Try this drink.

267
00:21:23,740 --> 00:21:26,640
Carrot drinks
are good for girls.

268
00:21:26,730 --> 00:21:28,200
Wow, thank you.

269
00:21:28,290 --> 00:21:30,810
You got no manners,
you brought just one?

270
00:21:30,920 --> 00:21:32,880
You hate carrots!

