01:10:08,530 --> 01:10:11,430
See how you're
being calculative?

790
01:10:11,620 --> 01:10:15,230
You pretend to be
naive on the outside,

791
01:10:16,070 --> 01:10:17,550
but calculating
everything on the inside.

792
01:10:17,610 --> 01:10:19,160
Aren't you the one
who feels guilty?

793
01:10:19,580 --> 01:10:20,620
What do you mean?

794
01:10:27,400 --> 01:10:30,080
When I said I was leaving
for Seoul with Ki-hoon,

795
01:10:31,450 --> 01:10:35,290
you were bawling,
but happy on the inside.

796
01:10:37,340 --> 01:10:38,540
No?

797
01:12:23,040 --> 01:12:24,820
<i>Autumn, 2012</i>

798
01:12:30,430 --> 01:12:34,730
You're worried about land
acquisition rate the most.

799
01:12:34,820 --> 01:12:38,630
As of yesterday, it's at 93,7%.

800
01:12:38,720 --> 01:12:41,540
You could say it's
all but confirmed.

801
01:12:42,000 --> 01:12:46,550
Wouldn't it be safer to
wait for regular pre-sale?

802
01:12:46,830 --> 01:12:48,770
You can only take advantage

803
01:12:48,860 --> 01:12:53,400
of pre-sale bonus when
you sign up before 95%.

804
01:12:53,780 --> 01:12:57,090
You know my agency
already invested in 2 lots.

805
01:13:02,030 --> 01:13:04,030
My office is upstairs.

806
01:13:05,330 --> 01:13:06,550
What do you do?

807
01:13:06,650 --> 01:13:09,580
I consult pre-sale lots,
but that's a side hustle.

808
01:13:09,620 --> 01:13:11,360
Main is investment.

809
01:13:18,600 --> 01:13:20,540
<i>Hanwool A&D</i>

810
01:13:21,050 --> 01:13:22,260
You can answer.

811
01:13:22,770 --> 01:13:25,570
It's the office,
I'll be up in a bit.

812
01:13:28,220 --> 01:13:29,600
What have you been up to?

813
01:13:30,990 --> 01:13:34,040
Ha-eun is assigned to a
school near her Jeju home,

814
01:13:34,420 --> 01:13:37,680
I'm studying for medical
licensing exam to become a doctor.

815
01:13:38,820 --> 01:13:40,450
Does she come to Seoul often?

816
01:13:40,500 --> 01:13:42,720
I go to her, you
know she can't fly.

817
01:13:43,950 --> 01:13:48,070
That's just an excuse, she
wants you to come to Jeju.

818
01:13:49,430 --> 01:13:51,370
You still don't know her well.

819
01:13:56,360 --> 01:13:59,210
You two? No contact?

820
01:14:02,730 --> 01:14:05,180
- Good bye!
- Bye!

821
01:14:08,440 --> 01:14:09,440
Come on!

822
01:14:14,230 --> 01:14:16,060
<i>Ahn Mi-so</i>

823
01:14:23,510 --> 01:14:25,400
<i>Hanwool A&D</i>

824
01:14:27,310 --> 01:14:30,260
Gotta go, the boss
must be looking for me.

825
01:14:31,600 --> 01:14:34,120
If it's important, please do.

826
01:14:34,240 --> 01:14:38,290
Half work, half pleasure,
the boss is my boyfriend.

827
01:14:39,550 --> 01:14:42,940
When his new business is
approved, and after all the pre-sales,

828
01:14:43,040 --> 01:14:44,840
we'll go live in Canada.

829
01:14:46,230 --> 01:14:48,090
When will you two get married?

830
01:14:54,890 --> 01:14:56,650
Janis Joplin

831
01:15:07,050 --> 01:15:10,350
I'll be in Canada next year,
so I won't be able to attend.

832
01:15:10,850 --> 01:15:12,770
congratulate her for me.

833
01:15:13,690 --> 01:15:14,690
I gotta go.

834
01:15:21,350 --> 01:15:22,660
We've arrived,
paramedics are heading up!

835
01:15:25,520 --> 01:15:26,400
Which office?

836
01:15:26,490 --> 01:15:28,490
506. Hanwool A&D.

837
01:15:28,600 --> 01:15:29,600
Hurry!

838
01:15:29,700 --> 01:15:32,040
Paramedics on the way!

839
01:15:52,020 --> 01:15:53,760
- Hurry - Where are you?

840
01:15:57,080 --> 01:15:58,990
I have to go in!

841
01:15:59,100 --> 01:16:01,440
You can't go in there! Please stop!

842
01:16:01,570 --> 01:16:03,560
Why can't I go?!

843
01:16:03,690 --> 01:16:06,840
- Please calm down.
- Stop!

844
01:16:35,090 --> 01:16:36,240
Let go of me!

845
01:16:36,320 --> 01:16:37,600
Calm down please.

846
01:16:37,940 --> 01:16:39,280
Mi-so.

847
01:16:49,940 --> 01:16:50,940
Let go!

848
01:16:51,060 --> 01:16:52,420
Get it together!

849
01:17:02,600 --> 01:17:04,110
<i>Jin-woo</i>

850
01:17:08,830 --> 01:17:12,370
<i>The person you are
calling is unavailable...</i>

851
01:17:12,760 --> 01:17:16,740
<i>Where are you?
Call me when you can.</i>

852
01:17:49,960 --> 01:17:51,440
Ha-eun.

853
01:17:55,590 --> 01:17:57,240
I missed you...

854
01:18:03,310 --> 01:18:04,310
Open the door.

855
01:18:15,140 --> 01:18:16,550
You stay out.

856
01:18:30,260 --> 01:18:31,480
Ha-eun...

857
01:18:35,780 --> 01:18:41,220
My lover died recently.

858
01:18:43,990 --> 01:18:50,240
He wasted all my
money and killed himself.

859
01:18:50,870 --> 01:18:56,250
So i was kicked out of my
room before I could move out.

860
01:18:58,520 --> 01:19:00,360
That's why I came here...

861
01:19:27,430 --> 01:19:29,120
So tired...

862
01:19:44,400 --> 01:19:46,670
Do it if you want to...

863
01:19:50,920 --> 01:19:53,050
You wanted to for a long time.

864
01:19:54,900 --> 01:19:55,900
What?

865
01:20:03,170 --> 01:20:05,480
Jin-woo isn't watching,

866
01:20:07,030 --> 01:20:10,240
so do whatever you want.

867
01:20:13,450 --> 01:20:15,410
How could you say that?

868
01:20:18,460 --> 01:20:19,700
Please...

869
01:20:21,540 --> 01:20:24,300
Just spill it!

870
01:20:25,210 --> 01:20:28,080
Don't keep
everything inside you.

871
01:20:29,720 --> 01:20:33,700
Or just leave me alone!

872
01:20:35,660 --> 01:20:38,680
I'm so sick and
tired because of you.

873
01:20:40,690 --> 01:20:42,610
Sick and tired?

874
01:20:43,480 --> 01:20:46,280
I'm the one who's
sick and tired!

875
01:20:50,700 --> 01:20:53,160
Had you thought
of me even a little.

876
01:20:53,990 --> 01:20:55,790
No, if you thought of us,

877
01:20:55,860 --> 01:20:58,030
you wouldn't be wearing this!

878
01:21:01,040 --> 01:21:07,590
You don't know why
I'm wearing this...

879
01:21:07,700 --> 01:21:09,770
Yeah, I don't know anything.

880
01:21:10,880 --> 01:21:15,050
You're always the victim,
and the one who has it had.

881
01:21:16,260 --> 01:21:20,040
You don't care why people
around you have it bad.

882
01:21:25,940 --> 01:21:28,880
You said you'd never
wear stuff like this.

883
01:21:30,120 --> 01:21:32,070
And yet you wear it?

884
01:21:35,950 --> 01:21:38,150
Jin-woo doesn't like this style.

885
01:21:42,460 --> 01:21:46,330
He likes these, take a look.

886
01:21:46,390 --> 01:21:47,180
No, please!

887
01:21:47,240 --> 01:21:51,630
Look at it carefully!
He likes tacky bras!

888
01:21:53,470 --> 01:21:55,510
I'm sorry, Ha-eun...

889
01:21:56,800 --> 01:21:58,140
Stop it...

890
01:22:04,770 --> 01:22:07,170
Did you sleep with him?

891
01:22:13,060 --> 01:22:14,060
No...

892
01:22:15,310 --> 01:22:18,210
Ha-eun, no...

893
01:22:18,880 --> 01:22:23,270
Do you think people
around you all loved you?

894
01:22:26,240 --> 01:22:30,540
Your lover, your mom, Jin-woo...

895
01:22:31,570 --> 01:22:36,080
do you think any of
them truly loved you?!

896
01:22:37,040 --> 01:22:39,310
You got no one except me!

897
01:22:39,630 --> 01:22:44,800
No one in this world
ever loved you except me!

898
01:22:48,010 --> 01:22:49,010
You're right.

899
01:22:53,190 --> 01:22:55,740
Without you, I'm nothing...

900
01:23:06,540 --> 01:23:09,780
How did we end up like this?

901
01:23:36,920 --> 01:23:37,920
Ha-eun...

902
01:23:56,750 --> 01:23:58,750
Thank you for
everything, Jin-woo.

903
01:24:27,940 --> 01:24:29,460
Lend me this.

904
01:24:29,990 --> 01:24:30,990
What?

905
01:24:31,540 --> 01:24:35,450
You said this kept you
alive, I think I need this.

906
01:24:36,790 --> 01:24:39,390
I don't want to
die until I'm 27.

907
01:25:30,810 --> 01:25:34,130
<i>I'm unavailable at the moment.</i>

908
01:25:35,920 --> 01:25:36,920
<i>Mi-so.</i>

909
01:25:41,390 --> 01:25:43,540
<i>A month went by.</i>

910
01:25:44,560 --> 01:25:47,080
<i>I didn't want to
think about anything,</i>

911
01:25:47,690 --> 01:25:51,950
<i>but you can't force your
mind to take a break.</i>

912
01:26:00,050 --> 01:26:02,060
I moved out of my
Seoul apartment.

913
01:26:02,460 --> 01:26:03,870
I want to prep
for the exam here.

914
01:26:06,080 --> 01:26:10,270
I'll spend the rest of
my life making up to you

915
01:26:11,590 --> 01:26:13,130
for all my mistakes...

916
01:26:45,690 --> 01:26:48,750
<i>We decided to get
married after his exam.</i>

917
01:26:48,890 --> 01:26:53,790
<i>and started living in a Jeju
house provided by his parents.</i>

918
01:26:58,860 --> 01:27:00,450
<i>It was a bit scary.</i>

919
01:27:01,130 --> 01:27:05,060
<i>It was my first
time leaving home.</i>

920
01:27:13,090 --> 01:27:15,230
- Ha-eun.
- Yeah?

921
01:27:15,620 --> 01:27:20,430
Should we head to Seoul
when we have a child?

922
01:27:22,000 --> 01:27:23,000
Why?

923
01:27:23,210 --> 01:27:26,150
There's difference in salary.

924
01:27:26,640 --> 01:27:29,220
and I want to be
where the opportunity is.

925
01:27:31,980 --> 01:27:35,640
I'm not sure, I never
thought about living in Seoul.

926
01:27:37,130 --> 01:27:38,810
This was my dream,

927
01:27:40,760 --> 01:27:42,640
just like you
becoming a teacher.

928
01:27:50,040 --> 01:27:52,640
I never wanted to be a teacher.

929
01:27:52,990 --> 01:27:53,990
Huh?

930
01:27:56,200 --> 01:27:58,860
I never once wanted
to be a teacher.

931
01:27:59,900 --> 01:28:02,980
What do you mean? Then why go to teachers college?

932
01:28:07,520 --> 01:28:12,280
Should I give up teaching
and learn to paint?

933
01:28:13,660 --> 01:28:14,660
Paint?

934
01:28:16,920 --> 01:28:20,040
I always liked painting
ever since I was a kid.

935
01:28:20,960 --> 01:28:23,840
I know you draw so well.

936
01:28:25,900 --> 01:28:28,170
Actually, when we first met.

937
01:28:28,410 --> 01:28:32,060
I was so shocked by that
drawing, it was incredible.

938
01:28:33,800 --> 01:28:35,120
- Really?
- Yeah.

939
01:28:36,380 --> 01:28:37,660
But Ha-eun,

940
01:28:38,430 --> 01:28:40,400
could you leave it as a hobby?

941
01:28:40,920 --> 01:28:45,210
Drawing realistically
is a skill, not a talent.

942
01:28:54,320 --> 01:28:57,230
Yes, slightly to this
way, oh, very good!

943
01:28:57,330 --> 01:28:59,010
Please smile widely!

944
01:28:59,560 --> 01:29:03,260
Very nice, hold it, one, two!

945
01:29:07,020 --> 01:29:08,020
Thank you.

946
01:29:08,450 --> 01:29:09,970
Thank you so much for coming.

947
01:29:11,360 --> 01:29:12,640
Family. please!

948
01:30:39,160 --> 01:30:43,650
<i>It was selfish, and I
felt bad for everyone.</i>

949
01:30:45,060 --> 01:30:47,100
<i>but it was my best.</i>

950
01:30:49,770 --> 01:30:52,870
<i>After the big wave washed
over, my mind became clearer.</i>

951
01:30:55,050 --> 01:30:56,980
<i>I decided to leave Jeju.</i>

952
01:31:11,960 --> 01:31:15,340
- Were you disappointed?
- Sure I was.

953
01:31:16,380 --> 01:31:19,300
If I wasn't, I'd be an angel.

954
01:31:22,260 --> 01:31:25,600
I'm sorry I didn't get to
live the life you wanted.

955
01:31:26,680 --> 01:31:28,810
What's the life I
wanted for you?

956
01:31:30,960 --> 01:31:35,440
You know, a normal life.

957
01:31:41,050 --> 01:31:45,950
Do you know why
every face is different?

958
01:31:47,090 --> 01:31:52,290
So that they can
all live different lives.

959
01:31:55,460 --> 01:31:59,550
Turns out, there
is no set way of life.

960
01:32:01,470 --> 01:32:03,430
Live the way you want to.

961
01:32:04,840 --> 01:32:07,240
That's what I really want.

962
01:32:59,510 --> 01:33:03,910
<i>I was always curious
about your home in Seoul.</i>

963
01:33:05,150 --> 01:33:06,990
<i>It didn't feel unfamiliar.</i>

964
01:33:23,060 --> 01:33:27,490
<i>Maybe that's why I felt at home.</i>

965
01:33:28,330 --> 01:33:31,190
<i>It was quiet enough
to feel the time flow.</i>

966
01:33:41,550 --> 01:33:43,380
<i>And of course, lonely too.</i>

967
01:33:44,330 --> 01:33:47,040
<i>I thought of the faces I missed.</i>

968
01:33:51,310 --> 01:33:56,980
<i>Mom's face, dad's
face, Jin-woo's face...</i>

969
01:34:03,070 --> 01:34:08,330
<i>But the face I missed
the most was yours, Mi-so.</i>

970
01:34:25,070 --> 01:34:27,610
- Who is it?
- It's Mi-so.

971
01:34:27,700 --> 01:34:29,430
- Welcome.
- Hey there.

972
01:34:29,520 --> 01:34:31,010
I'm back.

973
01:34:31,220 --> 01:34:33,120
Good afternoon.

974
01:34:33,250 --> 01:34:36,050
She's the friend I told
you about, Ko Ha-eun.

975
01:34:36,120 --> 01:34:38,040
- Welcome.
- Hello.

976
01:34:38,120 --> 01:34:40,900
This is my landlord,
and Sung-yeon.

977
01:34:41,360 --> 01:34:44,370
Hi. I'm a tenant, just like Mi-so.

978
01:34:45,190 --> 01:34:46,550
You didn't have dinner yet?

979
01:34:46,650 --> 01:34:49,630
Go have a chat,
I'll get it ready.

980
01:34:49,760 --> 01:34:56,020
Crème de la crème
of our 28-course meal!

981
01:34:56,080 --> 01:34:57,680
Let's take a look.

982
01:34:57,750 --> 01:34:59,310
It's incredible.

983
01:34:59,830 --> 01:35:06,020
You don't eat like
this everyday, right?

984
01:35:06,090 --> 01:35:08,190
Of course not, how
would we do that?

985
01:35:08,260 --> 01:35:14,260
28 courses today, 72
yesterday and 146 2 days ago.

986
01:35:14,330 --> 01:35:17,080
Yeah, last week was
tough with 385 courses.

987
01:35:17,180 --> 01:35:19,370
We had food to the
door and ate for 4 days.

988
01:35:19,490 --> 01:35:22,150
Stop it, it's not funny.

989
01:35:23,970 --> 01:35:27,520
How did the three of
you came to live together?

990
01:35:27,620 --> 01:35:31,680
My husband passed away
and I looked for roommates,

991
01:35:31,780 --> 01:35:33,310
and to make some money.

992
01:35:33,410 --> 01:35:36,980
And Sung-yeon was
working at a restaurant.

993
01:35:37,050 --> 01:35:40,390
I was a regular, and
Mi-so was a waitress.

994
01:35:41,120 --> 01:35:44,010
This crab's a bit salty.

995
01:35:44,140 --> 01:35:45,140
Yeah?

996
01:35:47,880 --> 01:35:51,070
Sorry, I poured too much love.

997
01:35:51,840 --> 01:35:54,290
Stop it, it's cheesy.

998
01:35:54,400 --> 01:35:58,280
Cheesy? Want some nachos
to go along with it?

999
01:36:01,720 --> 01:36:02,830
Mi-so smiled, look.

1000
01:36:02,890 --> 01:36:04,330
Eat up.

1001
01:36:11,590 --> 01:36:12,590
I'm off.

1002
01:36:14,380 --> 01:36:16,340
Not scared of flying anymore?

1003
01:36:17,500 --> 01:36:21,670
It is a bit scary, but
squinting makes it okay.

1004
01:36:22,430 --> 01:36:25,570
Send me letters, I'm
not going anywhere.

1005
01:36:37,300 --> 01:36:40,220
This is M, and this is S.

1006
01:37:05,390 --> 01:37:06,940
<i>Mi-so, guess where I am.</i>

1007
01:37:07,120 --> 01:37:08,880
<i>I'm on the Trans-Siberia
train to Lake Baikal in Olkhon.</i>

1008
01:37:24,050 --> 01:37:26,820
<i>I realized something
while traveling.</i>

1009
01:37:28,390 --> 01:37:32,270
<i>We will live
different lives now.</i>

1010
01:37:40,780 --> 01:37:42,650
<i>You'll be like the old me...</i>

1011
01:37:54,460 --> 01:37:57,270
<i>and I'll be like the old you.</i>

1012
01:38:02,120 --> 01:38:04,280
<i>I realized something
while traveling. We will live different lives.</i>

1013
01:38:09,940 --> 01:38:12,960
Ms. Ahn, someone's look for you.

1014
01:38:21,940 --> 01:38:23,970
How did you know I worked here?

1015
01:38:24,560 --> 01:38:28,010
Raemi Gallery, I
asked the curator.

1016
01:38:29,910 --> 01:38:32,070
She told me you didn't
know Ha-eun very well.

1017
01:38:32,730 --> 01:38:35,310
It's not like I have to
tell her about everything.

1018
01:38:35,890 --> 01:38:39,190
Mi-so, tell me the truth.

1019
01:38:40,050 --> 01:38:41,380
Where is she now?

1020
01:38:41,450 --> 01:38:43,270
I told you, I don't know.

1021
01:38:43,960 --> 01:38:45,990
Why are you curious about her?

1022
01:38:46,060 --> 01:38:48,530
If you read her words,
you know why I'm curious.

1023
01:38:49,030 --> 01:38:51,970
She left like that
and didn't tell anyone.

1024
01:38:52,520 --> 01:38:54,480
Tell me, where is she now?

1025
01:38:54,600 --> 01:38:57,150
I told you, I don't know.

1026
01:39:00,110 --> 01:39:02,820
<i>Ha-eun</i>

1027
01:39:11,740 --> 01:39:12,740
Here you go.

1028
01:39:12,820 --> 01:39:13,820
Mom.

1029
01:39:14,420 --> 01:39:17,270
Did you have fun
with your friends?

1030
01:39:17,320 --> 01:39:18,170
Yes.

1031
01:39:18,210 --> 01:39:19,760
- What about lunch?
- I had curry.

1032
01:39:19,850 --> 01:39:22,180
Curry? That's what you loved.

1033
01:39:26,020 --> 01:39:28,100
<i>Ahn Ha-eun</i>

1034
01:39:28,230 --> 01:39:29,950
- Stay here for a bit.
- Okay.

1035
01:39:46,210 --> 01:39:50,320
Right, she's you
and Ha-eun daughter.

1036
01:41:06,070 --> 01:41:07,870
What does it feel like?

1037
01:41:11,910 --> 01:41:13,940
I can sometimes
feel her heartbeat.

1038
01:41:15,690 --> 01:41:16,690
It's pretty cool.

1039
01:41:20,170 --> 01:41:21,550
Does Jin-woo know?

1040
01:41:24,480 --> 01:41:25,480
No.

1041
01:41:29,650 --> 01:41:32,440
I left him at the altar.

1042
01:41:36,040 --> 01:41:39,710
